The paper deals with the problem of target tracking using robots, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The privacy-preserving aspect of the problem involves cryptography and security (cs.CR). The analysis of the problem involves modeling and control (cs.SY), as well as machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) to some extent. The paper also involves optimization and decision making (cs.LG) in finding the best tracking strategy.
